Date: 0/6/2008
Source: Footnotes
Author:
Vol / Page: 11
Edition:
Quote: Shore plover occurred throughout New Zealand until the mid-1800s. Introduced predators wiped them out on mainland New Zealand, and they were reduced to about 130 birds on Rangatira (South East) Island in the Chatham Islands.
